article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 86, Fla. International 68
article.story: LITTLE ROCK (AP) -- Terrance Akins scored 16 points, including 12 on 4-of-5 shooting from long-distance, to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to an 86-68 win Thursday night over Florida International in a Sun Belt Conference matchup. UALR (10-13, 5-7 SBC) nearly shut down FIU's offense in the first half, holding the Golden Panthers (9-13, 4-8) to only 29 percent shooting from the floor while the Trojans made 58 percent of their shots. The result was a 44-21 score at halftime. Despite adjustments that allowed FIU to improve its shooting accuracy to 53 percent after intermission, the visitors were able to make up only five points of the gap at halftime. Johwen Villegas of FIU led all scorers with 22 points -- including 5-of-10 from 3-point range -- while Alex Galindo added 14 and Chris Fuller scored 10. De'Andre Eggins scored 15 points for UALR, with Byron Ray coming off the bench to add 13 and Steven Moore scoring 10.
